summary:
Experienced petroleum exploration geologist, specialised in stratigraphy.
For 18 years employed by Shell International: Holland, UK, Oman, Malaysia, Nigeria and Australia. Next senior lecturer in petroleum geology at Curtin University in Perth, moved to Preussag Energie in Germany and next for 4 years with Gaz de France in The Netherlands. In 2010 moved from Svenska Petroleum Exploration in the UK to Centrica Energy in Holland. In early 2014 moved to E.ON E&P Norge AS and next to Petrobras Oil & Gas BV in Rotterdam until mid 2016. 
After retirement revisited biostratigraphical research and presently studying glacial deposits in The Netherlands.
